David Totton, 36, admitted driving a rented white Peugeot RCZ into club doors .
He was walking through Manchester city centre when bouncers refused to let him in .
Totton, who survived being shot in the head in 2006 as part of suspected assassination attempt, tried to claim attack was meant as a joke .
But judge ruled he was not meant to intimidate anyone and said it was 'a prank'